1:- Installtion 
1.Download Go.tar.gz file- through this 
https://golang.org/doc/install

2.Remove if directory present
sudo rm -rf /usr/local/go

3.Make a new directory and exctract to it
sudo tar -C /usr/local -xzf go1.16.5.linux-amd64.tar.gz

4. Add /usr/local/go/bin to the PATH environment variable. 
export PATH=$PATH:/usr/local/go/bin

5.Verify the version
go version


2:-Delete golang completely
sudo apt-get remove golang-go
sudo apt-get remove --auto-remove golang-go

3:-Update Golang
1.Delete
2.Reinstall

4:-To install golang in terminal
sudo apt-get install golang

5:-To get latest version of golang
sudo snap install --classic go
